(Bridge)
Friends and family, they politely sway,
While I play on, lost in my own way.

Somehow I'll keep at it, day by day,
Hoping someday, somehow I'll find my musical way.

They smile and nod, but I know what they mean,
"Please stop playing, that's not so serene."

They tap their feet and smile so wide,
But inside, I know, they want me to hide.

They say "it's cute" or "keep on trying",
But deep inside, I know I'm just not flying.
